<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="150" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="21.[171,1380,1953,3046]" pageId="21" pageNumber="150">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[174,528,2777,2810]" pageId="21" pageNumber="150">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Arlindo’s Short-tailed Opossum has not been assessed as a distinct species on The IUCN Red List because at the time of the last assessment, it was considered to be a conspecific with the Guyanan Short-tailed Opossum (
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Erxleben" baseAuthorityYear="1777" class="Mammalia" family="Didelphidae" genus="Monodelphis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Didelphimorphia" pageId="21" pageNumber="150" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="brevicaudata">Monodelphis brevicaudata</taxonomicName>
). Conservation status of all opossumsis being reassessed by the IUCN New World Marsupial Specialists Group.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
